 Variety comic, a self-created ‘Vamp’ and a character actor. Above all, this is a book that celebrates, with idiosyncratic humour and warmth, how these actors accomplished much of their best work during the transitional period between the Rank/ABPC roster of stars and the US domination of the British film industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aActorszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aActresseszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszGreat Britainy20th century. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2020. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aCharacter Acting.  aCinema.  aCinephile.  aHollywood funding.  aNational Identity.  aPatriarchy.  aSexism.  aSocial History.  aStardom.  aThe studio system.1 aRoberts, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614704240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526147042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526147042/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles